summary:
🐺 Arya Stark appreciation 18/- 

  Arya had not known her brother was so near. Riverrun was much closer than Winterfell, though...
caption:
🐺 Arya Stark appreciation 18/-

Arya had not known her brother was so near. Riverrun was much closer than Winterfell, though she was not certain where it lay in relation to Harrenhal. I could find out somehow, I know I could, if only I could get away. 

When she thought of seeing Robb’s face again, Arya had to bite her lip.

summary: all i ask: chapter four — eavesdropper
title: all i ask: chapter four — eavesdropper
body:
Fandoms / Pairing: A Song Of Ice And Fire / Gendrya
Series: Gendrya Week (3/?)
Words: 9,381
Chapter(s): 4/7
Rating: Teen+
AO3 / / FF.net

It’s a long while before Arya manages to fall asleep that night. She kept tossing and turning, feeling like a small child throwing herself around her big bed. All she could do was just stare at her ceiling in the dark, trying her hardest not to look at the numbers that were steadily changing on her clock. If she pushed herself, really pushed herself, she would throw her pride away and forget whatever feelings she felt for Gendry, and just call everything off right now.

It wouldn’t be a big deal. She might get a comment from Sansa before she went on to comfort her sister post breakup, but other than that, there would be no lasting consequences. Even though she knew Robb and Jon would question her incessantly about whether or not Gendry hurt her in any way, once they saw them acting completely normal, even they would let it all go.

But the thing was…Arya herself didn’t want to let this go. Not one bit. She had spent most of her younger years liking Gendry enough that she tried to hide from him when he was over the house. It took so long to get over those feelings, and she thought they were gone forever. And then he’d texted her that fateful night, and the next thing she knew, she was negotiating terms with him on a contract. A contract that meant nothing to either of them, but still. She could pull it out right now and she’d see it: Gendry’s signature, shaky from disuse, right next to Arya’s dramatically looping signature.

Every excuse in the entire world came in and out of her head that night as Arya tried to go to sleep. Every reason possible to not text Gendry right now that she was ripping up their contract. She’d gotten so good at fooling herself that if she wasn’t so unsure of herself right now, she’d probably believe it.

summary:
-Stupid cat-she said after hearing it purr at Jon-He gave me a hell of a time trying to catch him. 
-He keeps following me all...
body:
-Stupid cat-she said after hearing it purr at Jon-He gave me a hell of a time trying to catch him.

-He keeps following me all day around. I gave him nothing nor did anything special. He just… likes me. Why did you want to catch him to begin with?

-A long story. He does not seem to be afraid of Ghost-Arya looked at the wolf.

-No, he isn’t. I woke up last night and he was there snoring at my feet. He must walked past Ghost. He is not afraid of Rhaegal either.

-Of course he is not-replied Bran-He’s Balerion.

-Balerion? The dread?-asked Arya.

-He is Balerion, princess Rhaenys cat-Bran added. Jon looked at it. The black fur, the green eye…

-My sister’s cat-Jon caressed his soft ears. Bran nodded. Ghost raised his head and yawned.

-I am your sister-replied Arya. The cat hissed.

-Yes, you are-Jon calmed the animal-But she was too.

summary: And my second cosplay ever! It was for the Game of Thrones Season 7 premiere at my local geek pub. I didn’t have much time to...
caption:
And my second cosplay ever! It was for the Game of Thrones Season 7 premiere at my local geek pub. I didn’t have much time to throw something together so I bought an inexpensive dress, pants, and shirt at Goodwill (may the old gods and the new bless Goodwill) and distressed the living crap out of all of them, using the “small, precise scissor/hobby knife incisions which one then savagely rips at like a maniac” method.

I also made fake mud using a combination of water, white flour, and dollar store instant coffee, and with the help of my lovely boyfriend splattered it all over the outfit. The sandals are from Five below, and the burlap is from Joann. I made my face look slightly dirty using some cheap brown-colored eyeshadow.

The contacts are the Zombie White Screen Halloween Lenses from HoneyColor. They were cheap and were pretty convincing from 5-10 feet away. Seeing through them is a bit of a challenge since it’s solid white around the iris and mesh over the pupil, but I could see well enough to do basic everyday things. It did make it harder to enjoy the episode, though!

All in all, this was one of my most fun cosplays of a very badass character, and I very much enjoyed the whole process.

summary: It was very scary actually because it’s a real knife he was using, very close to my face, actually cutting the hair. It wasn’t...
caption:
It was very scary actually because it’s a real knife he was using, very close to my face, actually cutting the hair. It wasn’t any- it was real, actually cutting. It’s very aggressive and she’s just seen her dad get killed. She’s going through a lot…lots of things are running through her head at that point. This man is in her face, who she’s only ever met once, cutting off her hair, and she’s not sure what’s going on and why any of this is happening. 

- Maisie Williams (x)
